"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-grading-american-track-performances-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympic Games turned out to be an immensely successful outing for track and field athletes from the United States.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 110, \"end\": 123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.8603966876409057, \"rank\": 0.16223789972138142, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Seeing as each country is allowed three entrants in each individual event and one team for each relay, there were 48 events with 132 possible medals for any one county.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 293, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Americans outperformed and earned 34 medals \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 14 gold, 11 silver, and 9 bronze.\\u00c2  At a track meet filled with superlatives, there are bound to be questions about how performances compare across disciplines or which athletes most exceeded expectations.\", \"from\": 294, \"to\": 547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Who emerged on the world stage?\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Who went home devastated?\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This article will attempt to answer the ponderings of the hardcore fan by grading every runner from the United States at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 746, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 710, \"end\": 723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.8603966876409057, \"rank\": 0.16223789972138142, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Grading Details  Grant Fisher earned bronze both in an excellent 10k field and a great 5k field.\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 844, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 765, \"end\": 777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Fisher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grant Fisher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Fisher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Fisher\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s now one of the world\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s best and, undoubtedly, the best-ever American distance runner.\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 914, \"end\": 922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997125309369572, \"rank\": 0.0002777117099453132, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His fitness is fantastic and his kick is now world-class.\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 997, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fisher\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s unprecedented success in the distance events on the track has changed the way the United States is perceived on the global stage.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1091, \"end\": 1104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.8603966876409057, \"rank\": 0.16223789972138142, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This pair of \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cminor\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d medals is transformative for Fisher, and for the USA.\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1194, \"end\": 1200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ronald_Fisher\", \"score\": 0.7854262910324556, \"rank\": 0.17355894457764082, \"text\": \"Fisher\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ronald_Fisher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ronald_Fisher\"}, {\"begin\": 1214, \"end\": 1217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9992600164013337, \"rank\": 0.00043405144651361056, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 400mH race isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t fun to watch anymore \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 Sydney has totally dominated it.\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1278, \"end\": 1284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9987934512211736, \"rank\": 0.0008241834695506164, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her result was predictable which is why superfans had been begging her to try the flat 400 or even the 200m, an event in which she had a promising early season result.\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Regardless of what could have been, Sydney performed at her absolute best with another world record in the 400mH and a masterful 400m leg in the 4x4.\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1629, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1516, \"end\": 1522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9987934512211736, \"rank\": 0.0008241834695506164, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both races were a pleasure to watch.\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1666, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sydney met expectations.\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1668, \"end\": 1674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9987934512211736, \"rank\": 0.0008241834695506164, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only surprise was her ridiculous 47.71 relay leg, but the team could have really used that in the mixed relay instead.\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Without the world record, this was an A-.\", \"from\": 1816, \"to\": 1857, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Inwinning 1500m gold, Cole Hocker dethroned Josh Kerr, Jakob Ingebrigtsen, and Yared Nuguse, each in their own way.\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 1974, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1903, \"end\": 1907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"score\": 0.7658143087026222, \"rank\": 0.3020860258785003, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\"}, {\"begin\": 1914, \"end\": 1932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jakob Ingebrigtsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\"}, {\"begin\": 1938, \"end\": 1950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yared_Nuguse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yared Nuguse\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yared_Nuguse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yared_Nuguse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He became the top American by defeating Nuguse.\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 2023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1994, \"end\": 2002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9993704990544048, \"rank\": 0.0006085163689961322, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He toppled the defending World Champion and self-proclaimed excellent kicker Josh Kerr.\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2101, \"end\": 2105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"score\": 0.7658143087026222, \"rank\": 0.3020860258785003, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He beat one of the greatest of all time, Jakob Ingebrigtsen, handily.\", \"from\": 2112, \"to\": 2181, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cole Hocker\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 1500m performance proved that he has the best kick in the world.\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It also proved what he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s been saying all season, that he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a much-improved runner who can kick off a fast initial pace.\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2387, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hocker winning in an Olympic record 3:27.65 still feels like a dream.\", \"from\": 2388, \"to\": 2457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He has totally shifted the landscape in this event, and it can be said that his success here inspired the American success that permeated through the rest of the competition.\\u00c2  Anna Cockrell took advantage of Femke Bol taking a risk to chase Sydney and scored a convincing silver medal in the low hurdles.\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2564, \"end\": 2572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9985752490398186, \"rank\": 0.0014043242336296794, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2635, \"end\": 2648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Cockrell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\"}, {\"begin\": 2667, \"end\": 2676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Femke Bol\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\"}, {\"begin\": 2700, \"end\": 2706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9990094900312975, \"rank\": 0.0008785622985917642, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last 50m of her race were a sight to behold as she destroyed Bol.\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 2833, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ignoring Femke Bol\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s altitude-aided 400mH PR set this year, Anna Cockrell\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 51.87 after two rounds now places her on nearly even footing with Bol heading into next season.\", \"from\": 2835, \"to\": 3010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2981, \"end\": 2984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cees_Bol\", \"score\": 0.99977149590758, \"rank\": 0.0001832197647124029, \"text\": \"Bol\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cees_Bol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cees_Bol\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rai Benjamin earned two Olympic golds.\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3012, \"end\": 3024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rai_Benjamin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rai Benjamin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rai_Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rai_Benjamin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 400m hurdles, he soundly defeated longtime rivals Karsten Warholm and Alison dos Santos.\", \"from\": 3051, \"to\": 3146, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3108, \"end\": 3123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karsten_Warholm\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karsten Warholm\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karsten_Warholm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karsten_Warholm\"}, {\"begin\": 3128, \"end\": 3145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alison dos Santos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\"}, {\"begin\": 3128, \"end\": 3145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alison dos Santos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 4 x 400m, he anchored the US team with a 43.1 split and scared the world record.\", \"from\": 3147, \"to\": 3234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3180, \"end\": 3182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.8877853357642637, \"rank\": 0.12635225868135086, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At age 27, Rai Benjamin has entered the prime of his career.\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3295, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3246, \"end\": 3258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rai_Benjamin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rai Benjamin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rai_Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rai_Benjamin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quincy Hall, who apparently ran the 400m final with an injury, managed a stunning comeback in the final 100m to win the race in one of the fastest performances of all time.\", \"from\": 3297, \"to\": 3469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3297, \"end\": 3303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"score\": 0.6396807105643936, \"rank\": 0.413808771016207, \"text\": \"Quincy\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hall, a former 400m hurdler, alluded to trying out different events in his post-race interview.\", \"from\": 3470, \"to\": 3565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He went from being a contender for bronze to a legend in the sport.\", \"from\": 3566, \"to\": 3633, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His injury kept him out of the 4 x 400m, and his absence there likely kept the USA short of the world record.\", \"from\": 3635, \"to\": 3744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3714, \"end\": 3717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997565301596073, \"rank\": 0.00018300663706376647, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rooks ran the most confident race of the Olympics with an early kick that almost dislodged Soufiane El Bakkali from his perch as the world\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s best and, indirectly, sent Lemecha Girma to the hospital  Despite kicking early and a late response by El Bakkali, Rooks found another gear to hold on to silver.\", \"from\": 3746, \"to\": 4050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3837, \"end\": 3856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_El_Bakkali\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Soufiane El Bakkali\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_El_Bakkali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_El_Bakkali\"}, {\"begin\": 3995, \"end\": 4002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zakaria_Bakkali\", \"score\": 0.9999993117909393, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bakkali\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zakaria_Bakkali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zakaria_Bakkali\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This race will be remembered as the most dramatic steeplechase race of this generation.\", \"from\": 4051, \"to\": 4138, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics presented a dreamlike scenario for Gabby Thomas as she won the 200m and ran on the USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gold-medal-winning relay squads.\", \"from\": 4140, \"to\": 4282, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4144, \"end\": 4158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only knock on her performance at the games was that, in the 4 x 100m, she gripped the baton awkwardly and passed it awkwardly, and so bears some responsibility for Sha\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Carri having to make up so much ground on the anchor leg.\", \"from\": 4283, \"to\": 4514, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gabby Thomas is this season\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s most exciting American sprinter.\", \"from\": 4516, \"to\": 4580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4516, \"end\": 4528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999990961192217, \"rank\": 9.038815389934464e-07, \"text\": \"Gabby Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\"}, {\"begin\": 4562, \"end\": 4570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9996555862836258, \"rank\": 0.00026630131869673554, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Noah Lyles defeated Kishane Thompson to win his \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cweak\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d event in a new PR of 9.78.\", \"from\": 4582, \"to\": 4667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4582, \"end\": 4592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 4610, \"end\": 4618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.5867998958817604, \"rank\": 0.7041571441148944, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He then contracted an illness and was good for just third in the 200m, an event where many thought he had a chance of breaking the world record.\", \"from\": 4668, \"to\": 4812, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t run the relay for the USA.\", \"from\": 4813, \"to\": 4851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4847, \"end\": 4850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998333372821826, \"rank\": 8.053546518053022e-05, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For an A, Noah needed a sub-9.70 100m, the double, or a legitimate crack at the WR.\", \"from\": 4853, \"to\": 4936, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4863, \"end\": 4867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Bennet\", \"score\": 0.8864732086601487, \"rank\": 0.06275396511884244, \"text\": \"Noah\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Bennet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Bennet\"}, {\"begin\": 4933, \"end\": 4935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_record\", \"score\": 0.9997088882578742, \"rank\": 0.0002911854921803166, \"text\": \"WR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_record\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_record\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jefferson fought for a hard-earned bronze in the 100m, taking advantage of the lack of Jamaicans in the final.\", \"from\": 4938, \"to\": 5048, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4938, \"end\": 4947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\", \"score\": 0.9999976035219628, \"rank\": 2.3964837823670762e-06, \"text\": \"Jefferson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\"}, {\"begin\": 5025, \"end\": 5034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999999261598332, \"rank\": 4.327889700813142e-08, \"text\": \"Jamaicans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She had a real chance of defeating a sloppy Sha\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Carri.\", \"from\": 5049, \"to\": 5105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She also passed the stick well in the relay final.\", \"from\": 5106, \"to\": 5156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Grant Holloway made a claim to GOAT status with a 12.99 performance in the 110mH.\", \"from\": 5158, \"to\": 5239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5158, \"end\": 5172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Holloway\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grant Holloway\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Holloway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Holloway\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t challenged by old or former rivals.\", \"from\": 5240, \"to\": 5287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was also nowhere near the world record of 12.80 or his PR of 12.81.\", \"from\": 5288, \"to\": 5358, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For an A, Grant needed sub 12.90 or a 4 x 100m relay leg.\", \"from\": 5359, \"to\": 5416, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Masai Russell won a tight gold in an exciting women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100mH race.\", \"from\": 5418, \"to\": 5485, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5418, \"end\": 5423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"score\": 0.9997600161459476, \"rank\": 0.00024004146012503326, \"text\": \"Masai\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maasai_people\"}, {\"begin\": 5424, \"end\": 5431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bertrand_Russell\", \"score\": 0.7389081948784414, \"rank\": 0.2970791626143468, \"text\": \"Russell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bertrand_Russell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bertrand_Russell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It would have been nice if she had broken the Olympic record of 12.26 by running at or below her PR of 12.25.\", \"from\": 5486, \"to\": 5595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Perennial favorite Jasmine Camacho-Quinn proved to be greatly diminished this year.\", \"from\": 5596, \"to\": 5679, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5615, \"end\": 5636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasmine_Camacho-Quinn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jasmine Camacho-Quinn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasmine_Camacho-Quinn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasmine_Camacho-Quinn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With Hoppel\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s last-minute entering and then last-last-minute pulling out of the 800m at the Monaco Diamond League, he was probably good for fifth in the Olympic field, behind Arop, Sedjati, Wanyonyi, and Tual.\", \"from\": 5681, \"to\": 5892, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5775, \"end\": 5781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monaco\", \"score\": 0.772315926766003, \"rank\": 0.2917145865355304, \"text\": \"Monaco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monaco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monaco\"}, {\"begin\": 5782, \"end\": 5796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"score\": 0.9891945715848132, \"rank\": 0.010915459488871746, \"text\": \"Diamond League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He ended up beating Tual and destroying the American record with a 1:41.67 for fourth place.\", \"from\": 5893, \"to\": 5985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5937, \"end\": 5945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9714272124348496, \"rank\": 0.026121370885724374, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rest of those names did beat him and beat him convincingly.\", \"from\": 5986, \"to\": 6049, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This result has to be one of the most frustrating results for any athlete at these Olympics.\", \"from\": 6051, \"to\": 6143, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 800 was taken to a new level this season, and though Hoppel met the challenge at the biggest stage, he finished just off the medal stand.\", \"from\": 6144, \"to\": 6293, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If Hoppel ran down Sedjati for third on the home straight, it would have meant an essentially perfect outing for the American men at these Olympics.\", \"from\": 6295, \"to\": 6443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6412, \"end\": 6420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9987080816476083, \"rank\": 0.0008256847531402011, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vernon Norwood will go down in history as one of the most consistent, likable, and fast 400m runners of his era.\", \"from\": 6445, \"to\": 6557, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6445, \"end\": 6459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vernon_Norwood\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vernon Norwood\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vernon_Norwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vernon_Norwood\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a PR of 44.10, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hard to believe that he has never stood on the podium at a major championship.\", \"from\": 6558, \"to\": 6663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s won 11 global relay medals, including two at World Indoors.\", \"from\": 6664, \"to\": 6730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6716, \"end\": 6729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics_Indoor_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Indoors\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics_Indoor_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics_Indoor_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Norwood gets the A- here because his patient 43.6 saved the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 4 x 400m preliminary after Quincy Wilson\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s disastrous opening leg.\", \"from\": 6732, \"to\": 6868, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6732, \"end\": 6739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwood_Football_Club\", \"score\": 0.9999709344659282, \"rank\": 2.9066345077290377e-05, \"text\": \"Norwood\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwood_Football_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwood_Football_Club\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also ran an outstanding 43.3-second leg in the final.\", \"from\": 6869, \"to\": 6925, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Also, he was flawless in the mixed 4 x 400m, in which the United States broke the world record.\", \"from\": 6926, \"to\": 7021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6984, \"end\": 6997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9311272096351473, \"rank\": 0.07351917649088024, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hobbs Kessler put together one hell of a season.\", \"from\": 7023, \"to\": 7071, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7029, \"end\": 7036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cosmo_Kramer\", \"score\": 0.8083330111531716, \"rank\": 0.23335573920812933, \"text\": \"Kessler\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cosmo_Kramer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cosmo_Kramer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After going pro out of high school, the 21-year-old American has emerged as a dual threat on the world stage.\", \"from\": 7072, \"to\": 7181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7124, \"end\": 7132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9987080816476083, \"rank\": 0.0008256847531402011, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He ran 3:29.45 to finish fifth in the 1500m final just behind Jakob Ingebrigtsen.\", \"from\": 7182, \"to\": 7263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7244, \"end\": 7262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jakob Ingebrigtsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Incredibly, this meant he was the third American finisher.\", \"from\": 7264, \"to\": 7322, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7304, \"end\": 7312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.995156484588491, \"rank\": 0.003359926285335679, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Through the rounds, he ran like a seasoned pro.\", \"from\": 7323, \"to\": 7370, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If he does continue competing this season, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s likely he can hit 3:28 in a paced 1500m.\", \"from\": 7371, \"to\": 7461, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 800m was more of a victory lap considering the relatively low expectations coming into the Olympics.\", \"from\": 7463, \"to\": 7567, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kessler was eliminated in his semifinal after finishing way back in 1:46.20.\", \"from\": 7568, \"to\": 7644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7568, \"end\": 7575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cosmo_Kramer\", \"score\": 0.9998989453712334, \"rank\": 7.167256763421513e-05, \"text\": \"Kessler\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cosmo_Kramer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cosmo_Kramer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bronze in the 100m was not the finale Fred Kerley was hoping for.\", \"from\": 7646, \"to\": 7711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7684, \"end\": 7695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Kerley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a turbulent season that saw him part ways from his sponsor and saw him drop out of the mainstream conversation as a 100m contender, a medal of any color brings serious vindication.\", \"from\": 7712, \"to\": 7895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The final was tight, and Kerley\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s strong start placed the pressure on Kishane Thompson which caused him to tie up early and lose to Noah Lyles.\", \"from\": 7896, \"to\": 8041, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7976, \"end\": 7984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.8981520097861383, \"rank\": 0.11339726759499462, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 8030, \"end\": 8040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kerley\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 4 x 100m anchor leg was doomed due to multiple botched handoffs.\", \"from\": 8043, \"to\": 8118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Outleaning Rasheed Broadbent for silver behind his training partner had to have been a special moment.\", \"from\": 8120, \"to\": 8222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Roberts has proved now that if there is ever an instance where Grant isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t in a high hurdles race, he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the guy to beat.\", \"from\": 8223, \"to\": 8347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8286, \"end\": 8291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ulysses_S._Grant\", \"score\": 0.9999953220488174, \"rank\": 3.6638808586131748e-06, \"text\": \"Grant\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ulysses_S._Grant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ulysses_S._Grant\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s incredible about Roberts\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 performance is that his start was amazing and he staggered after making major contact with hurdle four.\", \"from\": 8349, \"to\": 8489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If he hadn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t bobbed hurdle three and then flopped four, he probably would have won gold.\", \"from\": 8490, \"to\": 8580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How is that for a reversal?\", \"from\": 8581, \"to\": 8608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nobody will remember Roberts\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 insane recovery early in the race, but it means that he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just as fast as Holloway now.\", \"from\": 8609, \"to\": 8730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8717, \"end\": 8725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Prison_Holloway\", \"score\": 0.9999351990799022, \"rank\": 3.728949401701412e-05, \"text\": \"Holloway\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q40357\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Prison_Holloway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Prison_Holloway\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Juliette Whittaker\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s performances through the rounds in Paris were epic.\", \"from\": 8732, \"to\": 8806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8790, \"end\": 8795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999919931807377, \"rank\": 8.006883291090687e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She ran 2:00.45, 1:57.76, and then 1:58.50 in the final.\", \"from\": 8807, \"to\": 8863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is one athlete whose \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009closs\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d in the final was actually a huge win.\", \"from\": 8864, \"to\": 8938, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dipping under 1:58 for a big PR in the semi was way beyond what anyone was expecting from her.\", \"from\": 8939, \"to\": 9033, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Coming back and giving a fast, honest effort in the final was delightful to watch.\", \"from\": 9034, \"to\": 9116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With no Athing Mu, a medal in the 800m would have crowned Whittaker the Next Great American, and one of the most surprisingly successful female performers of the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 9118, \"to\": 9294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9201, \"end\": 9209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9994172051157869, \"rank\": 0.0004165054753775339, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only Great Britain\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Georgia Bell (1500m bronze) ranks ahead of her on that list.\", \"from\": 9295, \"to\": 9378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9318, \"end\": 9325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"score\": 0.6279013835436548, \"rank\": 0.5690275015795729, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s marathon field was outstanding, and the course was considered to be grueling.\", \"from\": 9380, \"to\": 9469, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Who better to tackle this challenge than two former BYU standouts who have a reputation for gritty racing and consistent performances in big races?\", \"from\": 9470, \"to\": 9617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Conner Mantz and Clayton Young are both excellent road runners.\", \"from\": 9619, \"to\": 9682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9619, \"end\": 9631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conner_Mantz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Conner Mantz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conner_Mantz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conner_Mantz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In this grading scheme, though, their accomplishments have been combined into something singular, because the two seem to be better than the sum of their parts.\", \"from\": 9683, \"to\": 9843, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mantz, considered the superior athlete, ran bravely and was contesting for the lead at the halfway mark.\", \"from\": 9844, \"to\": 9948, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anyone who woke up at 3 a.m. EST to use the restroom would have been excited to see that.\", \"from\": 9949, \"to\": 10038, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By the end of the race, Young was just 32 seconds behind him as they finished eighth and ninth.\", \"from\": 10039, \"to\": 10134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The performance is significant because their finishing times, 2:08:12 and 2:08:44, were well under what would have been considered \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cgood\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d for an Olympic marathon.\", \"from\": 10136, \"to\": 10302, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic marathon courses are always slower than the flat courses used in major marathons.\", \"from\": 10303, \"to\": 10392, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The two men ran close to their all-time PRs and were within striking distance of the podium.\", \"from\": 10393, \"to\": 10485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was the closest thing to a \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cwin\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d that American distance running could have hoped to eek out of this crowded marathon field.\", \"from\": 10487, \"to\": 10619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10534, \"end\": 10542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9969545830647107, \"rank\": 0.0015330141660657368, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brittany Brown ran 22.20 to win bronze in the 200m behind Gabby Thomas and Julien Alfred.\", \"from\": 10621, \"to\": 10710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10621, \"end\": 10635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brittany_Brown\", \"score\": 0.999999714242831, \"rank\": 2.8573762634376915e-07, \"text\": \"Brittany Brown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brittany_Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brittany_Brown\"}, {\"begin\": 10679, \"end\": 10691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999522358768983, \"rank\": 4.7766403064957966e-05, \"text\": \"Gabby Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The story of the race was Gabby Thomas blowing everyone\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s doors off.\", \"from\": 10711, \"to\": 10781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10737, \"end\": 10749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999522358768983, \"rank\": 4.7766403064957966e-05, \"text\": \"Gabby Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brown should have been able to clip Julien Alfred for silver.\", \"from\": 10782, \"to\": 10843, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hard to believe that Christian Coleman failed to qualify for the US team at 100m or 200m.\", \"from\": 10845, \"to\": 10941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10873, \"end\": 10890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Coleman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian Coleman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Coleman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Coleman\"}, {\"begin\": 10917, \"end\": 10919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.8850507255823812, \"rank\": 0.12583433564759283, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The cloud hanging over him is that he hasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t been the same since returning from his suspension.\", \"from\": 10942, \"to\": 11039, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even though the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 4 x 100m team was disqualified as a result of Christian Coleman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s botched handoff to Kenny Bednarek, Coleman wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t at fault.\", \"from\": 11041, \"to\": 11194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11111, \"end\": 11120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Cage\", \"score\": 0.9930140301198481, \"rank\": 0.003614565652691634, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Cage\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Cage\"}, {\"begin\": 11152, \"end\": 11166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenny Bednarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\"}, {\"begin\": 11168, \"end\": 11175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derrick_Coleman\", \"score\": 0.7497463772123023, \"rank\": 0.30962097748787504, \"text\": \"Coleman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derrick_Coleman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derrick_Coleman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, Coleman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s opening split was one of the fastest ever recorded for the first turn in the relay.\", \"from\": 11195, \"to\": 11299, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a shame that Kenny Bednarek took off so early.\", \"from\": 11300, \"to\": 11353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11320, \"end\": 11334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenny Bednarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nuguse beat Jakob with a late kick.\", \"from\": 11355, \"to\": 11390, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11367, \"end\": 11372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"score\": 0.9999983588015592, \"rank\": 1.4039444681004884e-06, \"text\": \"Jakob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Somehow, beating Jakob at the Olympics meant settling for third place.Nuguse, considered to have the best engine and the best ability to compete head-to-head with Jakob, ran an uninspiring race.\", \"from\": 11391, \"to\": 11585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11408, \"end\": 11413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"score\": 0.9999983588015592, \"rank\": 1.4039444681004884e-06, \"text\": \"Jakob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\"}, {\"begin\": 11554, \"end\": 11559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"score\": 0.9999983588015592, \"rank\": 1.4039444681004884e-06, \"text\": \"Jakob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He now has to work through this mental block where Cole Hocker and Josh Kerr are capable of running insanely fast times and then kicking.\", \"from\": 11586, \"to\": 11723, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11653, \"end\": 11657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"score\": 0.9884286356815847, \"rank\": 0.01156806702643962, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re set to eat Nuguse\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s lunch every time it matters.\", \"from\": 11724, \"to\": 11784, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Though his tactics left something to be desired, this was a monumental performance for Nuguse and American middle-distance running in general.\", \"from\": 11786, \"to\": 11928, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His pulling out of the 1500m at the Paris Olympics is now forgiven.\", \"from\": 11929, \"to\": 11996, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lindwurm placed 12th in the Olympic Marathon.\", \"from\": 11998, \"to\": 12043, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11998, \"end\": 12006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindworm\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lindwurm\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindworm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindworm\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She showed true confidence in leading the race at some point, and her performance speaks to her massive potential in the event.\", \"from\": 12044, \"to\": 12171, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dakotah was a virtual unknown until this year, so though her performance is borderline A-minus, the back half of her race wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t quite at the same level as Mantz or Young.\", \"from\": 12172, \"to\": 12345, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12172, \"end\": 12179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sioux\", \"score\": 0.8870203250325308, \"rank\": 0.12736988294300045, \"text\": \"Dakotah\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sioux\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sioux\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Graham Blanks had to sit and wait for a bit after USAs to find out whether he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d be going to Paris.\", \"from\": 12347, \"to\": 12447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12347, \"end\": 12353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin_Graham\", \"score\": 0.9999997598053203, \"rank\": 1.324038120059243e-07, \"text\": \"Graham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q188094\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin_Graham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin_Graham\"}, {\"begin\": 12441, \"end\": 12446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999706725496743, \"rank\": 2.932831041598562e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old from Harvard came back from injury during this outdoor season to not just qualify for the Olympic games, but to finish 9th in the final in 13:18.67.\", \"from\": 12448, \"to\": 12612, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 5k final saw a late surge of pace that really only started rolling with 600m to go.\", \"from\": 12614, \"to\": 12701, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Up until that point, Blanks ran a composed race and stuck with the leaders.\", \"from\": 12702, \"to\": 12777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He closed in 55.9 but was outside of the camera shot on the last lap.\", \"from\": 12778, \"to\": 12847, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Behind Blanks, however, were 13 athletes, many of them seasoned pros.\", \"from\": 12848, \"to\": 12917, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was a dream performance for Blanks.\", \"from\": 12918, \"to\": 12958, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nico Young ran a brave race and stuck with 12 of the world\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s best distance runners until the very end.\", \"from\": 12960, \"to\": 13064, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12960, \"end\": 12970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nico_Young\", \"score\": 0.9999966571931674, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nico Young\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nico_Young\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nico_Young\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He beat Woody Kincaid by over 30 seconds and finished 15 seconds off of the podium.\", \"from\": 13065, \"to\": 13148, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was a massive result for a college kid, albeit one who has been accompanied by massive expectations since high school.\", \"from\": 13149, \"to\": 13272, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nico continues to improve season after season, and those who followed him in high school will recognize him now as a comprehensively better runner.\", \"from\": 13274, \"to\": 13421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His performance differs from Blanks\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 in that the 10k was a higher-quality field and a more competitive race, in terms of how close the times were to the world record.\", \"from\": 13422, \"to\": 13590, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There was immense pressure on Chris Bailey to anchor the Quincy-Wilson-weakened 4 x 400m relay team to a qualifying spot.\", \"from\": 13592, \"to\": 13713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13622, \"end\": 13634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Bailey_(musician)\", \"score\": 0.6860807969265442, \"rank\": 0.41060446977649356, \"text\": \"Chris Bailey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Bailey_(musician)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Bailey_(musician)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He ran a measured race and a strong 44.0 to slot the United States into third.\", \"from\": 13714, \"to\": 13792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13767, \"end\": 13780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9311571031578626, \"rank\": 0.07081875353681547, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also ran a strong leg in the final.\", \"from\": 13793, \"to\": 13831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bailey\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s sixth-place finish in the 400m final was disappointing, but it came after he set a new PR of 44.31 in the semifinal.\", \"from\": 13833, \"to\": 13960, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nothing more could have been asked of Christopher Bailey.\", \"from\": 13961, \"to\": 14018, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13999, \"end\": 14017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christopher_Bailey_(fashion_designer)\", \"score\": 0.9861421604285604, \"rank\": 0.014051522248243986, \"text\": \"Christopher Bailey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christopher_Bailey_(fashion_designer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christopher_Bailey_(fashion_designer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His future is bright.\", \"from\": 14019, \"to\": 14040, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kenny Bednarek was a popular pick for second in the 200m.\", \"from\": 14042, \"to\": 14099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14042, \"end\": 14056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenny Bednarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He finished ahead of (sick) teammate Noah Lyles but behind Botswana\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Letsile Tebogo.\", \"from\": 14100, \"to\": 14187, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14137, \"end\": 14147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also showed major improvements in the 100m this year, qualifying for the US team, making the final, and finishing seventh in 9.88.\", \"from\": 14188, \"to\": 14321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14264, \"end\": 14266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6883599563748102, \"rank\": 0.448510810541459, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, Bednarek\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s early takeoff as the second leg of the USA men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 4 x 100m relay team will be remembered as one of the most devastating gaffes in professional sprinting.\", \"from\": 14323, \"to\": 14505, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bednarek took off too early, Christian Coleman couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t catch him, and he kept the USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s curse in this relay alive.\", \"from\": 14506, \"to\": 14625, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The team was disqualified.\", \"from\": 14626, \"to\": 14652, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This one will haunt him and he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll spend the rest of his career making amends.\", \"from\": 14653, \"to\": 14732, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Silver behind Julien Alfred is going to sting.\", \"from\": 14734, \"to\": 14780, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a sentiment that Sha\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Carri regressed at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 14781, \"to\": 14845, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Through the rounds, her start was never where it needed to be.\", \"from\": 14846, \"to\": 14908, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the final, her reaction time was laughably slow.\", \"from\": 14909, \"to\": 14960, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Without any of the Jamaican trio from Budapest in the final, SCR had a relatively easy path to silver.\", \"from\": 14961, \"to\": 15063, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14980, \"end\": 14988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9996538581083423, \"rank\": 0.00034591732026308363, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}, {\"begin\": 14999, \"end\": 15007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 0.9999968041403144, \"rank\": 3.167047162628484e-06, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\"}, {\"begin\": 15022, \"end\": 15025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Signal_Corps_Radio\", \"score\": 0.7872990532230248, \"rank\": 0.2566978501876587, \"text\": \"SCR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Signal_Corps_Radio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Signal_Corps_Radio\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She ran an unimpressive 10.87 behind Julien Alfred for the biggest anticlimax to any American storyline.\", \"from\": 15064, \"to\": 15168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15149, \"end\": 15157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999085315110314, \"rank\": 8.853963082980845e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 4 x 100m final, Sha\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Carri anchored the team to an easy gold.\", \"from\": 15170, \"to\": 15239, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She shot an intimidating glance to her right once she knew she had cleared the field.\", \"from\": 15240, \"to\": 15325, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Though Deadmon ran a snappy 43.54 in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 4 x 400m final, his 44.66 in the mixed relay final contributed to the United States getting kicked down by the Netherlands.\", \"from\": 15327, \"to\": 15499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15446, \"end\": 15459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997737996986783, \"rank\": 0.00014769263883122023, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 15487, \"end\": 15498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6744816740638997, \"rank\": 0.478483812464363, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s been a solid performer on the US relay squad, but the 44.66 here exposes him to some scrutiny.\", \"from\": 15500, \"to\": 15601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15537, \"end\": 15539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9983895999728537, \"rank\": 0.0015056075760116327, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Parker Valby finished 11th as the third American in a global final.\", \"from\": 15603, \"to\": 15670, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15603, \"end\": 15609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Parker\", \"score\": 0.8181886960863579, \"rank\": 0.22195757817730558, \"text\": \"Parker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Parker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Parker\"}, {\"begin\": 15610, \"end\": 15615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valby\", \"score\": 0.9999999997861551, \"rank\": 2.1389366209268383e-10, \"text\": \"Valby\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valby\"}, {\"begin\": 15643, \"end\": 15651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999850387058795, \"rank\": 8.074329539219844e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why she outranks the two Americans who beat her is that she is relatively inexperienced, still riding the high of a collegiate season for the ages and that she actually made a move toward the lead later in the race.\", \"from\": 15671, \"to\": 15886, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not much to analyze here, aside from Parker Valby being the real deal, and her having a higher racing IQ than previously suspected (she has led pretty much every other race she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s ever competed in).\", \"from\": 15887, \"to\": 16096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15934, \"end\": 15940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Parker\", \"score\": 0.8181886960863579, \"rank\": 0.22195757817730558, \"text\": \"Parker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Parker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Parker\"}, {\"begin\": 15941, \"end\": 15946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valby\", \"score\": 0.9999999997861551, \"rank\": 2.1389366209268383e-10, \"text\": \"Valby\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valby\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Joining Parker Valby as the third American, but in the 5k, Wittni Morgan outranks her compatriots because she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s relatively new to the pro ranks and managed to run a personal best in the final in less-than-ideal conditions.\", \"from\": 16098, \"to\": 16322, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16106, \"end\": 16112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Parker\", \"score\": 0.8181886960863579, \"rank\": 0.22195757817730558, \"text\": \"Parker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Parker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Parker\"}, {\"begin\": 16113, \"end\": 16118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valby\", \"score\": 0.9999999997861551, \"rank\": 2.1389366209268383e-10, \"text\": \"Valby\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valby\"}, {\"begin\": 16132, \"end\": 16140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999850387058795, \"rank\": 8.074329539219844e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 16164, \"end\": 16170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_Grimes\", \"score\": 0.543326665711816, \"rank\": 0.45019346606048594, \"text\": \"Morgan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_Grimes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_Grimes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Morgan ran 14:53.57 for 14th.\", \"from\": 16323, \"to\": 16352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16323, \"end\": 16329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_Grimes\", \"score\": 0.543326665711816, \"rank\": 0.45019346606048594, \"text\": \"Morgan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_Grimes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_Grimes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By all accounts, this is a B performance for her.\", \"from\": 16353, \"to\": 16402, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TeeTee qualified for the 100m final and placed fifth.\", \"from\": 16404, \"to\": 16457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She has emerged as a world-class sprinter in the absence of the Jamaicans and also established herself as a role player for Team USA, running an excellent 9.98 in the second leg of the 4 x 100m final.\", \"from\": 16458, \"to\": 16658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16522, \"end\": 16531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999415994478419, \"rank\": 5.627258160324054e-05, \"text\": \"Jamaicans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alexis Holmes ran 50.00 and then a PR of 49.77 in the 400m final.\", \"from\": 16660, \"to\": 16725, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16667, \"end\": 16673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"score\": 0.9996165901004588, \"rank\": 0.00038353456945067985, \"text\": \"Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That performance only earned her sixth place.\", \"from\": 16726, \"to\": 16771, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She closed well in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 4 x 400m relay, running 48.78 which was second, in absolute terms, only to Femke Bol\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 48.62.\\u00c2  These two women ran very good mixed 4 x 400m legs.\", \"from\": 16772, \"to\": 16953, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kaylyn Brown\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s strong anchor leg in the prelim secured the world record in this young event for the United States.\", \"from\": 16954, \"to\": 17070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17056, \"end\": 17069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.5538170511628668, \"rank\": 0.8034665253562995, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, Shamier Little and Kaylyn Brown were outclassed by Lieke Klaver and Femke Bol in the final, running 49.39, 49.23 to 49.26, 48.00.\", \"from\": 17071, \"to\": 17215, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17137, \"end\": 17149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lieke_Klaver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lieke Klaver\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lieke_Klaver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lieke_Klaver\"}, {\"begin\": 17154, \"end\": 17163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Femke Bol\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States ended up with silver here, losing to the Netherlands by .29.\", \"from\": 17216, \"to\": 17294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17220, \"end\": 17233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.5538170511628668, \"rank\": 0.8034665253562995, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 17275, \"end\": 17286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9942053656797748, \"rank\": 0.005810171830673982, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not so much that these two women failed, but the US was punished for not running their best women in this event.\", \"from\": 17296, \"to\": 17415, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17352, \"end\": 17354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999218058686321, \"rank\": 0.00033166168818038266, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shamier Little also ran the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 4 x 400m, and had an outstanding opening leg that set the stage for Sydney\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s epic 47.71.\", \"from\": 17417, \"to\": 17545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Grace Stark ran a great 12.43 for fifth place in the 100mH final.\", \"from\": 17547, \"to\": 17612, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17553, \"end\": 17558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stark_Street\", \"score\": 0.9809779802042237, \"rank\": 0.01939085920647183, \"text\": \"Stark\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stark_Street\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stark_Street\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In such a tight race, a slightly different execution and one error from a competitor could have meant a medal for Stark.\", \"from\": 17613, \"to\": 17733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17727, \"end\": 17732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stark_Street\", \"score\": 0.9458823563488674, \"rank\": 0.05651001055983892, \"text\": \"Stark\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stark_Street\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stark_Street\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She slowed over the final three hurdles but showed she has all the tools to compete at this level.\", \"from\": 17734, \"to\": 17832, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kelati and Schweizer finished eighth and ninth in the 10k.\", \"from\": 17834, \"to\": 17892, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17845, \"end\": 17854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schweizer_Aircraft\", \"score\": 0.9994600261143358, \"rank\": 0.0005402634276029205, \"text\": \"Schweizer\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schweizer_Aircraft\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Schweizer_Aircraft\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aside from two or three surges that ended up not making a difference, these women were uninteresting pack runners.\", \"from\": 17893, \"to\": 18007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The United 