be disappointed with not making the 400mH final.\", \"from\": 18363, \"to\": 18439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18370, \"end\": 18377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Bassitt\", \"score\": 0.9999999999996589, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bassitt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Bassitt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Bassitt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His 48.29, quite a bit off what he ran at USAs, was good for fourth in a brutal semifinal that featured Alison dos Santos and Karsten Warholm.\", \"from\": 18440, \"to\": 18582, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18544, \"end\": 18561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alison dos Santos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\"}, {\"begin\": 18544, \"end\": 18561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alison dos Santos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_dos_Santos\"}, {\"begin\": 18566, \"end\": 18581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karsten_Warholm\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karsten Warholm\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karsten_Warholm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karsten_Warholm\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Considering only the top two auto-qualified and that dos Santos ahead of him nabbed a time qualifier, Bassitt was in a difficult position.\", \"from\": 18583, \"to\": 18721, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18685, \"end\": 18692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Bassitt\", \"score\": 0.9999999999996589, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bassitt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Bassitt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Bassitt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He ended up getting edged out for the second time qualifying spot by .09.\", \"from\": 18722, \"to\": 18795, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CJ Allen also did not advance past the semis.\", \"from\": 18797, \"to\": 18842, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18797, \"end\": 18799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OGN_Entus\", \"score\": 0.6052840646543016, \"rank\": 0.6159086774133646, \"text\": \"CJ\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OGN_Entus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OGN_Entus\"}, {\"begin\": 18800, \"end\": 18805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ray_Allen\", \"score\": 0.9887321128242136, \"rank\": 0.011385464424393945, \"text\": \"Allen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ray_Allen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ray_Allen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He ran 48.44 for fourth in his heat which placed him one spot behind Bassitt in the compiled results from the semis.\", \"from\": 18843, \"to\": 18959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18912, \"end\": 18919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Bassitt\", \"score\": 0.99999999999784, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bassitt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Bassitt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Bassitt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both men ran well and were incredibly close to the promised land, but they ended up just short of the final.\", \"from\": 18960, \"to\": 19068, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t a strong showing from the United States in the one-lap race.\", \"from\": 19070, \"to\": 19144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19110, \"end\": 19123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9992530243510223, \"rank\": 0.00037980108660555327, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kendall Ellis had to qualify for the semi through the repechage round, and then she and Aaliyah Butler found themselves far outside of qualifying for the final.\", \"from\": 19145, \"to\": 19305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19145, \"end\": 19158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kendall_Ellis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kendall Ellis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kendall_Ellis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kendall_Ellis\"}, {\"begin\": 19233, \"end\": 19240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aaliyah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.674689748655378e-15, \"text\": \"Aaliyah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aaliyah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aaliyah\"}, {\"begin\": 19241, \"end\": 19247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Butler_Bulldogs_men's_basketball\", \"score\": 0.9932213657322597, \"rank\": 0.005786013563126543, \"text\": \"Butler\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Butler_Bulldogs_men's_basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Butler_Bulldogs_men's_basketball\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ellis outranks Butler here for running 50.44 in the repechage and 50.40 in the semi, but they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re both in the C range.\", \"from\": 19306, \"to\": 19425, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19321, \"end\": 19327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Butler_Bulldogs_men's_basketball\", \"score\": 0.9932213657322597, \"rank\": 0.005786013563126543, \"text\": \"Butler\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Butler_Bulldogs_men's_basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Butler_Bulldogs_men's_basketball\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In qualifying for the US team, Allie Wilson staked her claim to have moved beyond her national class designation.\", \"from\": 19427, \"to\": 19540, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19449, \"end\": 19451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9988479292543699, \"rank\": 0.000372479902139797, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, though, she ran like a national class athlete, with a 1:59 in a tough first round and then another 1:59 in the repechage.\", \"from\": 19541, \"to\": 19672, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19544, \"end\": 19549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999518740319991, \"rank\": 4.81282837770379e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She would not have been a factor in the final, but it would have been good practice for her to take a major shot in the semis like Juliette Whittaker did.\", \"from\": 19673, \"to\": 19827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19804, \"end\": 19812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliette_Peirce\", \"score\": 0.6944669902073031, \"rank\": 0.439953246702729, \"text\": \"Juliette\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliette_Peirce\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliette_Peirce\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Allie Wilson will need a big offseason to make the team again in 2025.\", \"from\": 19828, \"to\": 19898, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19834, \"end\": 19840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C._J._Wilson\", \"score\": 0.990133595429988, \"rank\": 0.005932702173802094, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C._J._Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C._J._Wilson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s been a long season for McKenzie Long, who just graduated from Ole Miss.\", \"from\": 19900, \"to\": 19978, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She qualified for the 200m final but ran an unimpressive final, finishing seventh in 22.42.\", \"from\": 19979, \"to\": 20070, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She really, really should have been able to take down the Brits Dina Asher-Smith and Daryll Neita.\", \"from\": 20071, \"to\": 20169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20156, \"end\": 20168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daryll Neita\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Knighton didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t live up to expectations this year.\", \"from\": 20171, \"to\": 20223, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20171, \"end\": 20179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ramsbury\", \"score\": 0.999952797925893, \"rank\": 4.024059695072948e-05, \"text\": \"Knighton\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ramsbury\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ramsbury\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The doping case against him, which is likely not yet settled, now casts doubt on his ascension as a teenager to the top of the sport.\", \"from\": 20224, \"to\": 20357, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was expected to get creamed by Lyles, Bednarek, and Tebogo at the Paris Olympics, and that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s exactly what happened.\", \"from\": 20358, \"to\": 20478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20392, \"end\": 20397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9985022283196232, \"rank\": 0.001483675226810034, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fourth place in this event is brutal, and with a 19.99 in the final, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s probably time for him to shut down his season.\", \"from\": 20479, \"to\": 20601, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Courtney Wayment stuck with the chase pack for most of the race but didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have anything on the last lap.\", \"from\": 20603, \"to\": 20710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20603, \"end\": 20611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courtney_Force\", \"score\": 0.9925083266431097, \"rank\": 0.007548220687633369, \"text\": \"Courtney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courtney_Force\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courtney_Force\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She finished way back in the field and far off her PR of 9:06.\", \"from\": 20711, \"to\": 20773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To be clear, there was no hope of medaling in this field, but a 9:05 or 9:06 would have taken her to a B-range grade.\", \"from\": 20774, \"to\": 20891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Crittenden\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s presence on the US team meant a real chance of a podium sweep in the 110mH.\", \"from\": 20893, \"to\": 20983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20924, \"end\": 20926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.6391193913554786, \"rank\": 0.5636360439452093, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As defending Olympic champion Hansle Parchment struggled through the rounds, this seemed even more likely.\", \"from\": 20984, \"to\": 21090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21014, \"end\": 21030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hansle_Parchment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hansle Parchment\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hansle_Parchment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hansle_Parchment\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Crittenden only finished sixth in the final.\", \"from\": 21091, \"to\": 21135, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21091, \"end\": 21101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Crittenden,_Kentucky\", \"score\": 0.8533500299143437, \"rank\": 0.10061528835123855, \"text\": \"Crittenden\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Crittenden,_Kentucky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Crittenden,_Kentucky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Oddly, he didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have any clear rhythm breaks during the race, he just looked flat.\", \"from\": 21136, \"to\": 21221, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"13.32 is not a fast time.\", \"from\": 21222, \"to\": 21247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Something went wrong for him.\", \"from\": 21248, \"to\": 21277, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Emily Sisson\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 2:29:53 for 23rd makes her the poster child for middling performances in the long-distance races.\", \"from\": 21279, \"to\": 21393, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wilkinson was a dark horse this year.\", \"from\": 21395, \"to\": 21432, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As fate would have it, his Paris qualifying heat was\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093by far\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093the fastest of the three, and he finished one second and one spot from qualifying.\", \"from\": 21433, \"to\": 21579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21460, \"end\": 21465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999984581291936, \"rank\": 1.541894563636027e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was, surely, a disappointing end for him, but his 8:16.82 essentially equaled his personal best.\", \"from\": 21580, \"to\": 21681, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Miller let himself get swept to the repechage round, then won his repechage heat, then found himself too far off the pace in his 800 semifinal.\", \"from\": 21683, \"to\": 21826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Miller put in three quality 800s at the Olympics but didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t ever show signs of being a medal threat, or even being able to match his sub-1:44 PR from USAs.\", \"from\": 21827, \"to\": 21984, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His performance does give credence to the idea that Clayton Young would have been a better dark horse here.\", \"from\": 21985, \"to\": 22092, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 1500m final started at breakneck pace and Elle was baited into running well beyond what she is capable of.\", \"from\": 22094, \"to\": 22204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22140, \"end\": 22144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elle_Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9657053535614881, \"rank\": 0.03296373054627009, \"text\": \"Elle\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elle_Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elle_Bishop\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She sat in second place as the leader went through 400m in 59.23, a nonsensical opener.\", \"from\": 22205, \"to\": 22292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That said, she earned her place on the rail and was composed enough to throw in a few surges before getting dropped by the leaders at 1200m.\", \"from\": 22293, \"to\": 22433, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If this was the 1500m of two years ago where it was Kipyegon and thenwhoever was willing to risk it, this strategy would have made more sense.\", \"from\": 22435, \"to\": 22577, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In today\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 1500m, three women finished under 3:53 and Jess Hull, who was considered a direct rival to Elle earlier this season, had already established herself as the silver medal favorite.\", \"from\": 22578, \"to\": 22779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22649, \"end\": 22653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingston_upon_Hull\", \"score\": 0.9984877737395131, \"rank\": 0.0005414992595632387, \"text\": \"Hull\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingston_upon_Hull\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingston_upon_Hull\"}, {\"begin\": 22692, \"end\": 22696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elle_Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9657053535614881, \"rank\": 0.03296373054627009, \"text\": \"Elle\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elle_Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elle_Bishop\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"St. Pierre holding on for a 3:57.52 was impressive, but she needed to emulate Laura Muir\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s sit-and-kick strategy if she wanted any shot at medals or a meaningful PR.\", \"from\": 22780, \"to\": 22947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22858, \"end\": 22863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9990521423693013, \"rank\": 0.0008925442981420117, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nikki Hiltz was flummoxed by the early pace and seemed to have trouble deciding how to run the 1500m final.\", \"from\": 22949, \"to\": 23056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22949, \"end\": 22960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikki_Hiltz\", \"score\": 0.9999994965741182, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nikki Hiltz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikki_Hiltz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikki_Hiltz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Considered a shoo-in for the final but an outside shot for a medal, Nikki finished seventh in 3:56.38 while never really beinginthe race.\", \"from\": 23057, \"to\": 23194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23125, \"end\": 23130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikki_Newman\", \"score\": 0.7149420647587197, \"rank\": 0.30376815987908795, \"text\": \"Nikki\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikki_Newman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikki_Newman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a way, there was a measured bet that a handful of runners ahead of her would falter, but Nikki only managed to kick down teammate Elle St. Pierre.\", \"from\": 23195, \"to\": 23344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23287, \"end\": 23292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikki_Newman\", \"score\": 0.7149420647587197, \"rank\": 0.30376815987908795, \"text\": \"Nikki\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikki_Newman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikki_Newman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Known for his excellent kick, Woody had realistic medal odds in a specific type of 10k: a slow one.\", \"from\": 23346, \"to\": 23445, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As soon as the pace picked up, a spectator could have said \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cwell, Kincaid is cooked now\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and would have been correct.\", \"from\": 23446, \"to\": 23567, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Woody fell off the pace fairly early and finished 16th in 27:29.40.\", \"from\": 23568, \"to\": 23635, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s still a world-class 10k guy, but he needed a pedestrian race.\", \"from\": 23636, \"to\": 23704, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Emily Mackay qualified for the semifinal but then ran a 4:02 for last place.\", \"from\": 23706, \"to\": 23782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23706, \"end\": 23711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Fields\", \"score\": 0.9983123429127422, \"rank\": 0.0008467565697456382, \"text\": \"Emily\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Fields\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Fields\"}, {\"begin\": 23712, \"end\": 23718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ken_Mackay\", \"score\": 0.8041052535160887, \"rank\": 0.24145649585342274, \"text\": \"Mackay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ken_Mackay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ken_Mackay\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t shouldering particularly heavy expectations, but her bombing out was surpassed only by Abdi Nur\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s trip.\", \"from\": 23783, \"to\": 23901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23883, \"end\": 23887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abdi,_Chad\", \"score\": 0.9999951102543214, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Abdi\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abdi,_Chad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abdi,_Chad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marisa Howard was a beneficiary of the openness of the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 3k steeple field in the US this year.\", \"from\": 23903, \"to\": 24005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23903, \"end\": 23916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marisa_Howard\", \"score\": 0.9999995357235262, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marisa Howard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marisa_Howard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marisa_Howard\"}, {\"begin\": 23992, \"end\": 23994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9543794960931555, \"rank\": 0.04567803008276019, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, she ran nowhere near her 9:07 PR from Eugene and finished 7th in the first round.\", \"from\": 24006, \"to\": 24102, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nia Akins finished third in her semifinal, failed to run a time qualifier, and did not advance to the 800m final.\", \"from\": 24104, \"to\": 24217, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The harsh grade is due to the perception that Akins, either in a world of hurt or not fully grasping the qualifying process, seemed to ease up at the end of her race.\", \"from\": 24218, \"to\": 24384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By easing up, Akins let what would have been an easy time qualifier (less than .5 seconds) slip away from her.\", \"from\": 24385, \"to\": 24495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Seeing as Mary Moraa wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t unbeatable this year and Athing Mu didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t qualify, Akins was America\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s best shot to medal in the 800m in Paris.\", \"from\": 24497, \"to\": 24642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 24507, \"end\": 24511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Shelley\", \"score\": 0.84460267615592, \"rank\": 0.10645271136313905, \"text\": \"Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Shelley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Shelley\"}, {\"begin\": 24636, \"end\": 24641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999775274180958, \"rank\": 2.247308662487359e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alaysha Johnson got off to a great start in the 100m hurdles final.\", \"from\": 24644, \"to\": 24711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 24652, \"end\": 24659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Johnson\", \"score\": 0.6867459851062155, \"rank\": 0.3788891237273579, \"text\": \"Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Johnson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was set to contend for a medal.\", \"from\": 24712, \"to\": 24747, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, she tripped on the third hurdle and appeared to let the field move away from her for the rest of the race.\\u00c2  With about 1k to go in the 3k steeplechase final, Constien began fading.\", \"from\": 24748, \"to\": 24944, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Once she knew she was out of it, she let the race get away from her, and finished in last place in 9:34.08.\", \"from\": 24945, \"to\": 25052, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She essentially gave up 10 seconds per lap for the last two laps.\", \"from\": 25053, \"to\": 25118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The critique here is that if someone is going to be okay with jogging home in an Olympic final, they should run much more aggressively than in the middle of the chase pack.\", \"from\": 25119, \"to\": 25291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After all the hype surrounding Korir\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s qualification to the games, he ran a disappointing 2:18.45 for 63rd place.\", \"from\": 25293, \"to\": 25408, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He ran near the back of the pack for most of the race.\", \"from\": 25409, \"to\": 25463, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Norman finished last in the 400m final in 45.62.\", \"from\": 25465, \"to\": 25513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 25465, \"end\": 25471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normans\", \"score\": 0.6836928732038224, \"rank\": 0.146709361678109, \"text\": \"Norman\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This result capped another uninteresting season for the combo sprinter who was once considered the premier talent in the 400m.\", \"from\": 25514, \"to\": 25640, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He put up 44.26 and 44.10 in the rounds, but he failed to hold it together in the final.\", \"from\": 25641, \"to\": 25729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a chance he picked up an injury, or that he had an injury all along, but this final was tailor-made for him.\", \"from\": 25730, \"to\": 25848, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His failure to medal in the context of the emergent Quincy Hall, the phenom Quincy Wilson, and the improving Christopher Bailey means Norman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s stock has fallen precipitously.\", \"from\": 25849, \"to\": 26025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 25901, \"end\": 25907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"score\": 0.7051261454933424, \"rank\": 0.307216744452459, \"text\": \"Quincy\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\"}, {\"begin\": 25925, \"end\": 25931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"score\": 0.7051738615469159, \"rank\": 0.307216744452459, \"text\": \"Quincy\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\"}, {\"begin\": 25932, \"end\": 25938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson\", \"score\": 0.5842041798340394, \"rank\": 0.40052964307871713, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson\"}, {\"begin\": 25958, \"end\": 25976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christopher_Bailey_(fashion_designer)\", \"score\": 0.9861421604285604, \"rank\": 0.014051522248243986, \"text\": \"Christopher Bailey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christopher_Bailey_(fashion_designer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christopher_Bailey_(fashion_designer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Abdi Nur fell at the tail end of his 5000m heat.\", \"from\": 26027, \"to\": 26075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 26032, \"end\": 26035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nur_Ahmed_Aman\", \"score\": 0.911551236614514, \"rank\": 0.09703102956198377, \"text\": \"Nur\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nur_Ahmed_Aman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nur_Ahmed_Aman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, the fall was his fault, and there was no way for him to qualify to the final on protest.\", \"from\": 26076, \"to\": 26179, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even without the fall, he likely wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t in a good enough position to advance.\", \"from\": 26180, \"to\": 26259, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Coming off a fairytale of a season in which he placed third at the US Trials and then ran a last-minute qualifying race at the University of Pennsylvania, Corrigan ran a poor 8:36.67 in the first round of steeple qualifying.\", \"from\": 26261, \"to\": 26485, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 26328, \"end\": 26337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"score\": 0.9999999933069148, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US Trials\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s possible that there was illness or injury at play, but a more likely scenario is that it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s been a long, long season for the rising BYU junior.\", \"from\": 26486, \"to\": 26637, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll now be thrown into Cross Country training as he hunts for NCAA titles this year.\", \"from\": 26638, \"to\": 26726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 26665, \"end\": 26678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cross_country_running\", \"score\": 0.9999768998211396, \"rank\": 2.2512548787937657e-05, \"text\": \"Cross Country\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cross_country_running\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cross_country_running\"}, {\"begin\": 26704, \"end\": 26708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9817274548580891, \"rank\": 0.018575199694931335, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quincy Wilson was one of the most-talked-about general interest stories of these Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 26728, \"to\": 26823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 26728, \"end\": 26734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"score\": 0.9450020540353374, \"rank\": 0.042765034037098734, \"text\": \"Quincy\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\"}, {\"begin\": 26735, \"end\": 26741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C._J._Wilson\", \"score\": 0.8987380628516739, \"rank\": 0.06480388800391798, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C._J._Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C._J._Wilson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 16 years old, the high school phenom is now the youngest Olympic gold medalist.\", \"from\": 26824, \"to\": 26906, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, Wilson was nursing an injury and his 47-second split placed the US men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s chances of advancing out of the preliminary rounds at risk.\", \"from\": 26907, \"to\": 27056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 26922, \"end\": 26928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C._J._Wilson\", \"score\": 0.8987380628516739, \"rank\": 0.06480388800391798, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C._J._Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C._J._Wilson\"}, {\"begin\": 26986, \"end\": 26988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9928442322006702, \"rank\": 0.0034934373364738456, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fiona O\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Keefe ran the Olympic Marathon with a bad injury.\", \"from\": 27058, \"to\": 27117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 27058, \"end\": 27063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiona_Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.8573802938174401, \"rank\": 0.16634326579713649, \"text\": \"Fiona\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiona_Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiona_Kennedy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She dropped back as the gun fired and DNF\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d early.\", \"from\": 27118, \"to\": 27170, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is still active debate as to the precise circumstances and whether she did indeed deprive the backup runner Jess McClain of a spot on the team, or if the injury came after the point that the team could have tapped an alternate.\", \"from\": 27171, \"to\": 27404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 27290, \"end\": 27297, \"title\": \"http://